Third-Party Licenses
====================

LDAPPortal uses the following open source libraries. This file documents
their licenses for compliance purposes.

LDAPPortal's own source code is split across two licensing tracks. The
edition-boundary doc (docs/edition-boundary.md) is the source of truth;
this section is a short pointer for anyone reading the licensing files
without reading the design docs:

  core/         Apache License 2.0
  addons/*      Apache License 2.0  (open-source optional modules;
                                     ISVA full-mode integration today,
                                     more to come — see edition-boundary.md)
  ee/           Proprietary, commercial license
                (LicenseRef-LDAPPortal-Commercial)

Every .java file under core/ and addons/ carries
`SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0`; every .java file under ee/ carries
`SPDX-License-Identifier: LicenseRef-LDAPPortal-Commercial`. CI grep
enforces the addons/ side.

The community distribution and the community-plus-isva distribution ship
nothing but Apache-2.0 code (boundary checks in each distribution module
fail the build if ee/ bytecode leaks in). The commercial distribution
bundles all three.

